{"parentUuid":"86c97eb8-6eda-4fb3-8280-d1c0877f543e","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01TPGtqNQ1HpBsnqQRquynjW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"There are a few ways depending on your situation:\n\n**If you already have the repo cloned locally:**\n```bash\ngit checkout <branch> -- path/to/file\n```\n\n**If you want to fetch from a remote without cloning the full repo:**\n\nUsing `git archive` (requires remote access):\n```bash\ngit archive --remote=<repo-url> HEAD path/to/file | tar -x\n```\n\n**Using sparse checkout (modern approach):**\n```bash\ngit clone --no-checkout --depth=1 <repo-url>\ncd <repo>\ngit sparse-checkout set path/to/file\ngit checkout\n```\n\n**Simplest one-liner with `curl` (GitHub/GitLab only):**\n\nFor GitHub:\n```bash\ncurl -O https://raw.githubusercontent.com/<user>/<repo>/<branch>/path/to/file\n```\n\nFor GitLab:\n```bash\ncurl -O https://gitlab.com/<user>/<repo>/-/raw/<branch>/path/to/file\n```\n\nWhich approach fits your case?"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1188,"cache_read_input_tokens":14555,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1188},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CZGPpoddyC8MZWJUmro7N","type":"assistant","uuid":"855e929c-2cf6-451d-a8a7-82074c83999a","timestamp":"2026-03-21T14:36:58.206Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/tymoyato","sessionId":"ded30bfe-b98a-41f3-bae3-9a228cdde4e1","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"HEAD"}
